Ask HN: Requesting feedback for debugging CI/CD for beginners book outline
text:
Hi. I am writing a book about debugging, speeding up, and profiling CI/CD for beginners. I would like your feedback on my outline regarding if you think this book would be useful for a beginner, and if the treatment of the topics is adequate.

I have a very messy outline here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/14iEQUTDqB-QdqEzvkvvN1qoCT0JfiNZKodfcMKaYI4w/edit

Looking forward to hearing your thoughts.

title: Ask HN: How to deal with being overqualified for a new job?
text: I accepted a job for a company that is safe from the recession and unlikely to be laid off.  The problem is that I am overqualified.  I don’t think I will be able to find another job given this economy and would not want to risk it with another company.  How should I deal with the nagging feeling I am wasting time for a guaranteed salary?

title: Ask HN: Cheapest Video Hosting?
text:
I’d like to let Screegle users upload their video screencasts online for a quick one link share option. Any recommendation? I looked at BackBlaze and it seems cheap and was able to upload files from my macOS app in Swift.

Are there other services besides the usual suspects?
